The paper discusses the key concepts behind Data Grids, which are a platform for scientific communities to share, access, transport, process, and manage large data collections distributed worldwide. This topic is related to distributed computing (cs.DC), distributed systems (cs.DS), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), and databases (cs.DB).
